<br>
I keep an eye on this board, so post a response if you want to set up a time for us to meet, or send me a tell in game.  im reliably online between 8pm-12am CST and 6am-7am CST and other times can be arranged, especially for weekends.<br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
Cleric 42<br>
Spirit Guardians <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubamilbanebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bamil Banebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/11/01 7:27:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EXP Groups</span><hr size=1> Just thought I'd throw in an update. I think the xp grouping is becoming more common, and I would hope that this trend continues. I have found that this is the only way to go. It has become almost unbearable to grab a pickup group, the only way I will xp hunt is if I know most of the people in the group. I have found that every SGA group I have been in has been productive, but most of all fun.<br>
<br>
As an example, Tuesday I devoted to xp camping most of the day. I grabbed a mostly SGA group in Karnor that consisted of Mondoli, Syrtic, Aarn, Myself, with Henklin and Softwind joining a bit later. Was an excellent group.<br>
<br>
That night we had a classic xp grind group and all SGA happen in the Hole. Those present were:<br>
<br>
Holt, 54 cleric Amnesty<br>
Bamil, 51 warrior SG<br>
Krytog, 50 shaman PoJ<br>
Kaelaeian 47 ranger PoJ<br>
Malleolus 51 wizard Amnesty<br>
Niema 51 enchanter Amnesty<br>
<br>
Was awesome fun. We cleared out the first 10 mobs in short order. And worked our way in. Only had 2 deaths.. both due to me ld'ing on a pull (blah), shouldn't have had any. For those that haven't been there that zone is intense. I would suggest it to all.<br>
<br>
So the moral of the story is, look up your SGA folk around your level and bug em to join you somewhere when you want xp groups. I am finding out that we have some of the best people on the server, and it will only further SGA to have everyone getting comfortable with our individual play styles.<br>
<br>
-BamBam<br>
51 Warrior<br>
